<div>
 <p>An ancient <strong>place</strong> is comprised of associations between
 ancient <strong>names</strong> and ancient <strong>locations</strong>.</p>

 <p>There are, at present, three ways to access records for the various 
 <a href="/help/places">places</a> documented in the Pleiades dataset:
 </p>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Search:</strong> type an <a href="/help/names">ancient or modern name</a> into the search box located in
            the upper right-hand corner of most pages in the site. Or go directly to the <a href="/search_form">advanced
                search form</a></li>
        <li><strong>Map:</strong> use our <a href="/places/map">dynamic map</a> (or link through it to Google Earth)</li>
        <li><strong>Browse thematically</strong>, via the categories listed below. <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Time periods</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <a href="archaic">Archaic (Pre-550 BC)</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="classical">Classical (550-330 BC)</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="hellenistic-republican">Hellenistic / Middle-to-Late Republican at Rome (330-30 BC)</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="roman">Roman (30 BC - AD 300)</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="late-antique">Late Antique (AD 300-640)</a>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Place types</strong> (note all types other than "settlement" are extra-urban) <ul>
                        <li>
                            <a href="bridge">Bridge</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="church">Church or monastery (extra-urban)</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="false">False place</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="fort">Fort or tower (extra-urban)</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="pass">Mountain pass, "gates"</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="station">Route or coastal station</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="settlement">Settlement</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="spring">Spring</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="temple">Temple, sanctuary, shrine, monument or tomb (extra-urban)</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="tumulus">Tumulus</a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="undefined">Undefined: i.e., a place whose type is not precisely defined, often an
                                unlocated toponym</a>
                        </li>
                    </ul></li>
            </ul></li>
    </ol>

    
  <p>For the benefit of search engines, the entire (warning: huge) listing is 
  <a href="all">here</a>.</p>

</div>
